  "texts": [
    "• Time Index.",
    "Due to the sparse distribution of ancient literature on the timeline, and the need to annotate publication years for a large volume of text, a timestamp based on the Common Era is not suitable for this data.",
    "As an alternative, we adopted the dynasty-level timestamp.",
    "Certainly, if scholars intend to develop a comparable platform for a more recent collection of texts that is more extensive and includes readily available time data, utilizing Common Era-based timestamps is undeniably the better choice.",
    "In our system, the time index table contains the dynasty names in Chinese history, with each dynasty assigned a unique identifier in chronological order."
  ],
